name: Surskit
flavorText: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Masquerain
flavorText: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may put a Pokemon Tool card attached to 1 of your Pokemon into your hand.

name: Lileep
flavorText: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokemon on the bottom of your deck.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Cradily
flavorText: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.
Attack1Text: For each Energy attached to this Pokemon, search your deck for a Stage 2 Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Tropius
flavorText: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Karrablast
flavorText: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

name: Shelmet
flavorText: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Accelgor
flavorText: When its body dries out, it weakens. So it wraps a membrane around itself for protection while it spits poison.
Attack1Text: If an Escavalier you had in play was Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, put all Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon into your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Virizion-EX
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokemon that has any Grass Energy attached to it can't be affected by any Special Conditions. (Remove any Special Conditions affecting those Pokemon.)
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Genesect
flavorText: This Pokemon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for 2 Grass Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Genesect-EX
Ability1Text: When you attach a Plasma Energy from your hand to this Pokemon, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with his or her Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness or Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Larvesta
flavorText: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: Thought to be an embodiment of the sun, it appeared during a bitterly cold winter and saved Pokemon from freezing.
Attack1Text: Reveal the top 5 cards of your deck and put all Team Plasma cards you find there into your hand. Discard the other cards.
Attack2Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: It shelters itself in its shell then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Blastoise
flavorText: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Lapras
flavorText: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Remoraid
flavorText: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Octillery
flavorText: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Suicune
flavorText: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon by Pokemon-EX.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Glalie
flavorText: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Move a Water Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Froslass
flavorText: It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degrees F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, your opponent can't attach any Special Energy cards from his or her hand to his or her Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Relicanth
flavorText: A rare Pokemon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.
Attack1Text: Put 2 Item cards that have Fossil in their names from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Snover
flavorText: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.

name: Abomasnow
flavorText: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.
Attack2Text: Both this Pokemon and the Defending Pokemon are now Confused.

name: Tirtouga
flavorText: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. It swam skillfully and dove to depths beyond half a mile.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokemon on the bottom of your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Carracosta
flavorText: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.
Attack1Text: You may discard an Item card that has Fossil in its name from your hand. If you do, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kyurem-EX
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.
Attack1Text: Discard as many Energy attached to your Pokemon as you like. This attack does 30 damage times the number of Energy cards you discarded.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Drifloon
flavorText: These Pokemon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Drifblim
flavorText: They carry people and Pokemon, but the wind can catch them, so there can't be a fixed destination.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Team Plasma Pokemon in play.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Uxie
flavorText: When Uxie flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Mesprit
flavorText: When Mesprit flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.
Ability1Text: If you have Uxie and Azelf in play, each of your Pokemon has no Weakness.

name: Azelf
flavorText: When Azelf flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Move as many Special Energy attached to your opponent's Pokemon to your opponent's other Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Munna
flavorText: This Pokemon appears before people and Pokemon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Musharna
flavorText: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards. This Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Sigilyph
flavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon may have up to 4 Pokemon Tool cards attached to it. (If this Pokemon loses this Ability, discard Pokemon Tool cards attached to this Pokemon until only 1 Pokemon Tool card remains.)

name: Solosis
flavorText: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Duosion
flavorText: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders psychically.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Golett
flavorText: Ancient science fashioned this Pokemon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

name: Golurk
flavorText: Golurk were created to protect people and Pokemon. They run on a mysterious energy.
Attack1Text: If you have any Team Plasma Pokemon in play, this attack does nothing.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Machop
flavorText: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.

name: Machoke
flavorText: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon's remaining HP is 10, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Machamp
flavorText: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.
Ability1Text: The damage of each of your Fighting Pokemon's attacks isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is increased by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Machamp
flavorText: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.
Attack1Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Throh
flavorText: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Does 80 damage minus 20 damage for each Colorless in the Defending Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Sawk
flavorText: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Team Plasma Pokemon, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Archen
flavorText: It was revived from an ancient fossil. Not able to fly, it lived in treetops and hopped from one branch to another.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokemon on the bottom of your deck.

name: Archeops
flavorText: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon's remaining HP is 50 or less, this attack's base damage is 50.

name: Houndour
flavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Houndoom
flavorText: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Team Plasma Pokemon, this attack does 60 more damage, and the Defending Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Aron
flavorText: In order to build up its steel body, it eats iron ore. This pesky Pokemon is known to eat railroad tracks.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Lairon
flavorText: Lairon fight over territory, and when their steel bodies collide, sparks fly.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Aggron
flavorText: It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don't take it lightly.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage to each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Jirachi-EX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack1Text: Both this Pokemon and the Defending Pokemon are now Asleep.

name: Escavalier
flavorText: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

name: Bagon
flavorText: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

name: Shelgon
flavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Salamence
flavorText: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon, you may discard all Pokemon Tool cards attached to each of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Discard any Stadium card in play.

name: Dialga-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, put a card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: For each Plasma Energy attached to this Pokemon, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Palkia-EX
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Heal from this Pokemon 20 damage for each Plasma Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Axew
flavorText: Its large tusks have a tendency to break, but each time they grow back, they grow in harder and sturdier.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Supporter card named Iris, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Fraxure
flavorText: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Haxorus
flavorText: Its tusks are incredibly destructive. They can easily slice through a thick, sturdy steel column every time.
Attack1Text: Does 40 damage times the amount of Metal Energy attached to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Team Plasma Pokemon, it is Knocked Out. (If the Defending Pokemon is not a Team Plasma Pokemon, this attack does nothing.)

name: Druddigon
flavorText: It runs through the narrow tunnels formed by Excadrill and Onix. It uses its sharp claws to catch prey.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokemon.

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby play only when it feels safe.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Porygon
flavorText: A man-made Pokemon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.

name: Porygon2
flavorText: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Porygon-Z
flavorText: Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Plasma Energy attached to 1 of your Pokemon to another of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Teddiursa
flavorText: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Ursaring
flavorText: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, each of this Pokemon's attacks does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Chatot
flavorText: Its tongue is just like a human's. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.
Attack1Text: Discard all Pokemon Tool cards attached to each of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: G Booster
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokemon.

name: G Scope
Attack1Text: This attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness or Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Virizion-EX
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokemon that has any Grass Energy attached to it can't be affected by any Special Conditions. (Remove any Special Conditions affecting those Pokemon.)
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Genesect-EX
Ability1Text: When you attach a Plasma Energy from your hand to this Pokemon, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with his or her Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness or Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Jirachi-EX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack1Text: Both this Pokemon and the Defending Pokemon are now Asleep.

name: Dialga-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, put a card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: For each Plasma Energy attached to this Pokemon, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Palkia-EX
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Heal from this Pokemon 20 damage for each Plasma Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: This extremely rare Pokemon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Virizion
flavorText: This extremely rare Pokemon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Leaf Wallop does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Dusknoir
flavorText: This extremely rare Pokemon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your opponent's Pokemon to another of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
